## Five. (20 points)

The relative motion relation between inertial frames S and S′ is shown in the figure. When O and O′ coincide, $t=t'=0$. Starting at $t'=0$, particle Q moves with constant velocity $u$ along the $x'$-axis in the S′ frame from $x'=L$, and particle P starts from rest with constant acceleration $a_0$ along the $x'$-axis in the S′ frame from $x'=0$, until P and Q collide. Set $L=u^2/2a_0$ and $v=u$, so the only known quantities are $a_0$ and $u$.

(1) Determine the collision time $t'$ between P and Q in the S′ frame;
(2) In the S frame, calculate the average acceleration $\bar{a}$ of particle P over the whole process from the moment $t=0$ when P starts accelerating until P collides with Q;
(3) With the conditions $L=u^2/2a_0$, $v=u$, and additionally setting $u=(\sqrt{2}-1)c$, compute $\bar{a}$ in part (2).
